consider we are leaders in innovative technology esi is a pioneer and leading supplier of worldclass production laser systems that help its microtechnology customers achieve compelling yield and productivity gains the companys industryleading applicationspecific products enhance electronicdevice performance in three key sectors — semiconductors passive components and electronic interconnect — by enabling precision finetuning of device microfeatures in highvolume manufacturing environments founded in  esi is headquartered in portland oregon if you are an experienced professional or an individual just beginning your career youll have the opportunity to spend your working hours on challenging projects that help shape the future of technology we provide a collaborative work environment where people enjoy what they do explore the jobs we have to offer  click to view esis equal opportunities  affirmative action program and the pay transparency nondiscrimination provision culture our mission develop design and deliver lasers laserbased systems and services that meet or exceed customer needs  our vision be seen by customers as the industry company of choice and premium value leader in laserbased micromachining applications across broad industry markets  our values  accountability we take ownership and responsibility for delivering results that meet the needs of our customers employees and shareholders  creativity our passion for innovation is at the heart of who we are and what we do  integrity we operate with the highest level of ethics and integrity in all aspects of our business  people we tackle complex challenges through teamwork and individual contributions  people are the key to our success  quality we embrace business processes that help to ensure high quality products and services are delivered to our customers  new college graduates join esi and your learning continues now that you have completed your degree your learning doesn’t stop it continues you will have an opportunity to take what you have gained in school and expand your knowledge by obtaining additional handson experience esi offers meaningful employment opportunities career development possibilities and an environment that recognizes and balances personal and professional needs whether youre a current student or have graduated in the last  months you may be eligible to be hired through our college recruitment program intern program gain handson realworld experience at esi internships provide both you and esi an opportunity to get to know each other an esi internship will help you gain handson realworld experience and develop practical skills that will assist you in your academic and career pursuits we are looking for ambitious students involved in undergraduate and graduate level programs in engineering or businessrelated fields excellent communication and teambuilding skills a former internship and relevant class or work experience are all advantages   for industries facing material transformation challenges in production  esi applies unique process and engineering expertise to deliver a set of laserbased solutions that extend our customers’ processing capabilities beyond the limitations of mechanical see what its like to be an esi customer  contact an esi sales expert today microvia drilling  electro scientific industries inc esi  new products  mar   photonics spectra menu photonics media buyers guide edu photonics register login publications news features products technologies education media webinars events subscribe advertise about us bookstore search this week in photonicslight matters monthly alertphotonics spectra newsletterbiophotonics newslettereurophotonics newsletterasiapacific photonics newsletterphotonics showcase newsletterspectroscopy newslettertradeshow sneak previewsindustrial photonics lasers newsletterindustrial photonics vision newsletterphotonics in defense  aerospace newsletterphotonics media bookstore alerttechnology newsletters about us bo