ncome taxes are recognized for the future tax consequences attributable to temporary differences between the financial statement and tax balances of existing assets and liabilities deferred tax assets and liabilities are measured using enacted tax rates expected to apply to taxable income in the years in which those assets and liabilities are expected to be recovered or settled the effect on deferred taxes resulting from a change in tax rates is recognized in income in the period that includes the enactment date when management determines that it is not more likely than not that a deferred tax asset will be fully realized a valuation allowance is established to reduce deferred tax assets to the amount expected to be realized  table of contents net deferred tax assets at march   and march   consisted of the following in thousands     deferred tax assets and liabilities       current       inventory valuation and warranty costs       receivables and other current assets       payrollrelated accruals     accrued liabilities     deferred revenue     other      total current deferred tax assets     valuation allowance current       net current deferred tax liability assets        noncurrent       deferred compensation       intangible assets and investments      accrued liabilities     property plant and equipment     other comprehensive income       tax loss and credit carryforwards     inventory valuation and warranty costs    — other —    total noncurrent deferred tax asset     valuation allowance noncurrent       net noncurrent deferred tax assets       total deferred tax assets       total valuation allowance       net deferred tax assets        table of contents the company had approximately  million and  million in tax assets resulting from federal state and foreign net operating losses and tax credits as of march   and march    respectively as follows in thousands     federal net operating losses      — state net operating losses     foreign operating losses and 